      "content": "That is a common misconception, but clarithromycin inhibits the metabolism of simvastatin regardless of the time of day, so taking them hours apart is dangerous. Because the drug interaction remains active in your system for a prolonged period, you must stop taking simvastatin completely while on clarithromycin. You should contact your doctor immediately to switch your cholesterol medication to something safe, like rosuvastatin or pravastatin, to avoid severe muscle injury.",
